How to use this list
Filter by specialism – payroll, SAP/SuccessFactors, change/adoption, talent strategy, etc.
Check Kununu or Glassdoor ratings if culture and work–life balance are deciding factors.
Look at client mix – some boutiques (e.g., smahrt, HCM ADVICE) thrive on SAP/SuccessFactors roll-outs; others (e.g., Kienbaum, PwC) cover broader people-strategy mandates.
Follow regional needs – if you target German federal clients, firms with BMI/öffentliche Verwaltung footprint (Kienbaum, BearingPoint) stand out; for Swiss multinationals, HR Campus and All for One dominate.
You can refine this master catalogue to a shortlist by industry fit, technology stack, or employer-branding score—then start networking or applying. Good luck in targeting the HR consultancies that fit your next career step!
Du:
