Application for HR Strategy Consultant (Remote)

Dear Hiring Team,

I was excited to discover your opening for an HR Strategy Consultant and would welcome the chance to strengthen Capgemini’s Workforce & Organization practice with my blend of strategic insight and hands-on HR-technology expertise.

In recent projects I analysed and refined HR strategies by conducting detailed gap analyses and co-creating digitalization roadmaps; this included re-designing and implementing processes across the entire employee lifecycle.

While introducing UKG HR Service Delivery, I guided clients from paper-based to fully digital HR services—launching a self-service dossier and case-management platform that shifted routine requests online and boosted service levels.

My authentic, enthusiastic communication style enables me to build trust from C-level to shop-floor employees and rally stakeholders behind shared goals. By linking IT-developers, CFOs, CTOs and HR teams I have repeatedly steered cross-functional projects to finish on time and within budget.

I bring solid data-analysis skills in Excel and Pivot-Tables and extend them with AI tools and ad-hoc Python scripts, allowing me to translate raw data into clear, actionable insights.

Working with a portfolio of 121 HR applications in a strict Best-of-Breed approach has given me broad market knowledge and the ability to recommend and integrate the optimal tool for each HR function.

To ensure adoption, I have delivered 100+ tailored workshops and trainings—from BPMN 2.0 to knowledge-base design and HR-service-center roll-outs—equipping users to embrace new ways of working.

Finally, I thrive in international settings: leading workshops in the USA and Canada with IT specialists in India and collaborating daily with multicultural teams has honed my intercultural communication skills.

With this background and a degree focused on HR strategy, I am confident I can help Capgemini align people strategies with business objectives and deliver measurable value to your clients. I look forward to discussing how my experience can contribute to your team’s continued success.

Kind regards

Manuel Weiss

