Subject – Application for Senior Integrations Consultant, Workday Success Plans (Flex Remote)

Dear Hiring Team,

ever since I began designing digital HR landscapes six years ago, I have believed that great software becomes truly valuable only when people understand it, trust it and continuously expand its possibilities. In my current role as Senior Consultant at HR Campus in Switzerland I have led remote integration projects for enterprise customers, turned complex HR requirements into secure cloud workflows and guided post-go-live teams through every question that arose afterwards. Those experiences—combined with an enduring curiosity and a gift for clear explanations—are exactly what draw me to the Workday Success Plans team.

My day-to-day work has revolved around short, high-impact consulting engagements: researching a client’s question, prototyping an integration, demonstrating its effect in a live tenant, then documenting “why it works” so the customer can extend it with confidence. I have configured and optimised case-management interfaces for more than 20 000 users, troubleshot integrations under tight deadlines and coached HR and IT stakeholders in plain language until new features felt second nature. The approach mirrors your micro-consulting model—answering how-to queries, offering targeted configuration advice and turning roadmap items into immediate business value.

Before joining HR Campus I worked as a process-management consultant and certified BPMN 2.0 trainer. Mapping end-to-end workflows taught me to ask the right questions early, see connections others miss and translate them into integration patterns that scale. While my recent focus has been the UKG platform, the methods, governance and security principles align closely with Workday’s Integration Framework, and I am eager to deepen my knowledge through Workday certification and daily customer work.

Eighteen months in Australia and a series of international projects have made English my working language alongside native German, and remote collaboration across continents has long been my routine. I enjoy travel when an on-site whiteboard session unlocks momentum, yet I deliver the same energy and clarity through a webcam when customers need quick answers.

Workday’s people-first culture resonates with my own conviction that satisfied, empowered teams build the best solutions. I would be delighted to bring my integration experience, presentation skills and passion for continuous learning to your Success Plans customers and help them discover even more value in their Workday investment.

Thank you for considering my application. I am available from August 2025 or by agreement and look forward to the opportunity to discuss how I can contribute to a brighter work day for all.

Kind regards

Manuel Weiss
weiss-manuel@gmx.de | +41 79 838 55 90

