Application for Solutions Architect

I discovered your posting on LinkedIn for the Solutions Architect role and would like to submit my application.

For more than six years I have guided customers through SaaS integrations that connect HR, payroll and learning systems to cloud platforms, most recently as Senior Consultant at HR Campus. There I translated business requirements into robust API designs, orchestrated SFTP batch synchronisations and managed SAML-based single-sign-on roll-outs for organisations with up to 20 000 frontline employees. Working between sales, product and engineering, I learned to frame technical concepts in language that resonates with both C-level sponsors and non-technical stakeholders, while steering projects in agile Kanban boards until every endpoint performed as promised.

Because integration is rarely a one-time event, I stay involved long after go-live, refining workflows, automating data quality checks and turning user feedback into epics for the product backlog. To deepen my developer toolkit I am currently completing an intensive Python course, driven by the wish to prototype transformation scripts and custom connectors myself rather than relying solely on others’ code. This complements my hands-on experience with Workato-style iPaaS configurations, where I assemble recipes, map complex data models and monitor run-time performance.

Beekeeper’s mission to improve the working lives of frontline teams matches my own enthusiasm for technology that truly serves people who are seldom digitised first. Your focus on scalable, purpose-built integrations appeals to the way I approach architecture: start with clear use cases, design for change and measure value in the day-to-day of end users. As a native German speaker with business-fluent English, I am comfortable switching languages in customer workshops and documentation, and I thrive in multicultural remote teams like the one you describe.

