Application as Solutions Architect
Dear Sir or Madam
I noticed your LinkedIn posting for a Solutions Architect and would like to apply for the position.

For more than six years I have led customers through SaaS integrations that connect HR systems to cloud platforms, most recently as a consultant at HR Campus. I translated business requirements into reliable workflows, orchestrated SFTP synchronisations, linked employee-data systems and delivered SAML-based single-sign-on—while meeting every project goal for time, budget and quality. Acting between sales and product management taught me to package technical concepts for C-level sponsors and non-technical stakeholders alike, steering work in Kanban as well as in classic project plans until every API endpoint performed as promised.

Because integration is seldom finished at go-live, I stay involved afterwards, refining processes and turning user feedback into practical solutions. To broaden my developer toolkit, I am currently completing an intensive Python course so that I can prototype transformation scripts and custom connectors myself.

Beekeeper’s mission to improve the working lives of frontline teams mirrors my own enthusiasm for technology that serves people who are rarely digitised first. Your focus on scalable, purpose-built integrations matches the way I design architecture: start with clear use cases, plan for change and measure value in the users’ everyday work. A native German speaker with business-fluent English, I switch languages effortlessly in workshops and documentation and enjoy working in multicultural remote teams.

